TextEng: Who, exactly, is your master?
Who master?
You're not exactly bright for a guard, are you?
Wizard hire dumb guard?
I am an intruder, obviously.
Me intruder, dummy.
My name is <FirstName>. Who are you?
Me <FirstName>. Who you?
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Err... I would be one of the master's friends. I'm here to see him.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 어... 나는 주인님의 친구 중 하나야. 그를 만나러 왔어.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Err... me master's friend. Here to see master.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 어... 나 주인 친구. 주인 보러 왔어.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> You don't need to challenge me. I wouldn't be here if I wasn't supposed to be, would I?
Text: <StartCheck>[통찰]</Start> 확인 할 필요 없어. 내가 올 자리가 아니었다면 여기 있겠어?

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Insight]</Start> So how would you know what one looks like, then?
Text: <StartCheck>[통찰]</Start> 그럼 어떻게 생긴 건지 네가 어떻게 안다는 거지?

TextEng: Nevermind that. I have some questions.
Not matter. Me have questions.
Just forget I was here. That should be easy.
Text: 내가 여기 있었다는 건 잊어버려. 쉬울 거다.

TextEng: You just not sees me, okay?
Text: 그냥 나 못 본 거야, 알겠지?

TextEng: Now you're just too smart for your own good. Time to die.
Text: 이제 넌 네 주제도 모르고 너무 똑똑한 척해. 죽을 시간이야.

TextEng: You too smart! Now you dies!!
Where exactly can I find your master?
What's beyond the door on your right?
What's beyond the door on your left?
What sort of guardians are there here?
Where master?
What behind door on your right?
What behind door on your left?
Your master - what he have guarding place?
Why would your master keep prisoners?
Text: 네 주인은 왜 죄수들을 가두는 거지?

TextEng: Why master have prisoners?
I have some questions for you.
Nevermind. I'll leave you to your... er... thoughts.
Text: 신경 쓰지 마. 네가... 어... 생각하게 둘테니까.

TextEng: Me have questions.
Is okay. Me leave you alone.
I just thought you should know your master is dead.
Me say your master is dead.
Text: 나 네 주인 죽었다고 말하는 거야.
